  • Wark the milk to luke warm, 37° C / 99F
  • Put the yeast in a bowl, 3-4 liter size. Pour the milk over and stir.
  • Add the butter, spoon by spoon, then add sugar, salt and the optional ground cardamon.
  • Add the flour, but save around 1/2 dl.
  • Knead the dough, 5 minutes by machine or 10 minutes by hand. It should be soft and smooth.
  • Cover the bowl with a clean towel and let proof for 30 minutes in room temperature.
  • Take the dough out of the bowl on to a surface sprinkled with flour.
  • Knead the dough lightly.
  • Divide into 4 pieces.
  • Roll the dough using a rolling pin to a rectangular shape.
  • Spread a 1/4 of the filling butter on the dough evenly (more butter isn't bad...), sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over the butter.
  • Roll up the dough from the long side.
  • Cut the roll in to 10 pieces and put them in paper baking cups (cut side up) on an oven rack.
  • Repeat 10-13 with the other 3 pieces.
  • Proof the buns under a clean towel for 40 minutes.
  • Pre-heat the oven to between 225° C and 250° C.
  • Brush with egg wash (crack the egg in a glass, mix it with a fork).
  • Add whatever toppings you'd like. Swedish tradition is to use pearl sugar.
  • Bake 5-10 minutes, when golden they're done.
  • Let cool on a grid under one of those clean towels.

    • Enjoy with a glass of milk!

    • 800 g Flour
    • 150 g Butter
    • 5 dl Whole Fat Milk (3-5% fat)
    • 50 g Yeast (for sweet dough)
    • 1 dl Granulated Sugar
    • 1/2 tbsp Salt
    • 2 tbsp Ground Cardamom (optional)

    Cinnamon Filling

    • 150 g Butter (room temp, spreadable)
    • 1 dl Granulated Sugar
    • 2 tbsp Cinnamon

    Toppings

    • 1 Egg
    • Whatever goodies you want to sprinkle on top
